      "reviewer_notes": "All 3 gates passed. An attacker can trigger this via P2P data availability sample by sending a commitment set to point-at-infinity (0xc00000...) with arbitrary cell data and proof, causing the batch verification to accept forged proofs because the infinity commitment contributes zero to the pairing equation while the weighted proof remains, creating an exploitable imbalance. Entry point is UNTRUSTED (P2P network). Impact: compromises PeerDAS data availability verification across all nodes via single malicious P2P packet.",
